# Qiniu Go SDK — Cursor Rules

## Project

Qiniu Cloud Go SDK (`github.com/qiniu/go-sdk/v7`). Go 1.22+, MIT License.
Provides Go clients for Qiniu Cloud services: object storage, CDN, live streaming, RTC, SMS, IoT, IAM, media processing, audit, and sandbox.

## Project Structure

- `auth/` — Authentication (AK/SK, signatures, tokens)
- `conf/` — Global config and version number
- `client/` — Base HTTP client
- `storage/` — Object storage v1 (Manager pattern: BucketManager, OperationManager, UploadManager)
- `storagev2/` — Object storage v2 (Provider/Interface pattern, generated APIs)
- `cdn/` — CDN acceleration
- `pili/` — Live streaming
- `qvs/` — Video surveillance
- `rtc/` — Real-time communication
- `sms/` — SMS service
- `linking/` — IoT device linking
- `iam/` — Identity and access management (generated APIs)
- `media/` — Media processing (generated APIs)
- `audit/` — Audit logging (generated APIs)
- `sandbox/` — Sandbox service (oapi-codegen + ConnectRPC generated)
- `internal/` — Internal packages (api-generator, clientv2 interceptor chain, cache, env, etc.)
- `api-specs/` — API specifications (git submodule)
- `examples/` — Usage examples

## Architecture Patterns

### Manager Pattern (storage v1)
- `BucketManager` — bucket/object management
- `OperationManager` — persistent data processing
- `UploadManager` — file uploads
- Constructed with `auth.Credentials`

### Provider/Interface Pattern (storagev2)
- `credentials.CredentialsProvider`
- `region.RegionsProvider`, `region.EndpointsProvider`
- `downloader.DownloadURLsProvider`

### Interceptor Chain (internal/clientv2)
- `Interceptor` interface: `Priority()` + `Intercept(req, handler)`
- Lower priority number = higher execution priority
- Built-in: auth, retry, anti-hijacking, headers, upload logging, debug

### Context-based Auth
- `auth.WithCredentialsType(ctx, cred, tokenType)` — inject credentials
- `auth.CredentialsFromContext(ctx)` — extract credentials

## Code Generation

Files marked `// THIS FILE IS GENERATED BY api-generator, DO NOT EDIT DIRECTLY!` are auto-generated.
- `storagev2/apis/`, `iam/apis/`, `media/apis/`, `audit/apis/` — from YAML specs via `internal/api-generator/`
- `sandbox/internal/` — from OpenAPI/Proto via `oapi-codegen` and `buf`
- Regenerate: `make generate` or `make generate-sandbox`

## Coding Conventions

- Format: `gofmt -s` (CI enforced)
- Static analysis: `staticcheck` (CI enforced)
- Comments: Chinese by default
- All exported identifiers must have doc comments starting with the identifier name
- Constructors: `New*()` or `New*Ex()`
- Error types: root `QError` (Code + Message) in `err.go`; typed errors in `storagev2/errors`

## Testing

- Unit tests: `//go:build unit` → `make unittest`
- Integration tests: `//go:build integration` → `make integrationtest`
- All tests: `make test`
- Framework: standard `testing` + `testify/assert`
- Mock: custom structs implementing interfaces (no frameworks)
- Prefer table-driven tests
- Tests exclude `examples/` and `sms/`

## Commands

- `make unittest` — run unit tests
- `make integrationtest` — run integration tests
- `make test` — run all tests
- `make staticcheck` — run static analysis
- `make generate` — regenerate API code
- `make generate-sandbox` — regenerate sandbox code

## Critical Rules

1. Never edit files marked `DO NOT EDIT DIRECTLY` — modify API specs then `make generate`
2. Run `make unittest` and `make staticcheck` before committing
3. Don't delete code in `sms/` or `examples/`
4. Version sync: `conf/conf.go`, `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`
5. `api-specs/` is a git submodule — init with `git submodule update --init --recursive`
